
[1]bird-lime

   BIRD'-LIME, n. [bird and lime.] A viscous substance,usually made of the
   juice of holly-bark, extracted by boiling, mixed with a third-part of
   nut oil or thin grease, used to catch birds. For this purpose, the
   twigs of a bush are smeared over with this viscid substance.
